data.description: Constructed in 1991, this custom-built home stands as a testament to meticulous craftsmanship and thoughtful design. The residence unfolds over a generous layout, featuring three well-appointed bedrooms and a dedicated office space, catering to both relaxation and productivity. The primary suite, strategically positioned on the main level, offers a haven of tranquility, complete with a large en-suite bathroom. The upper level houses two expansive guest bedrooms, which share a bathroom, ensuring comfort for residents and guests alike. One of the home's standout features is the vast walk-in attic storage space located above the garage, perfect for stowing away belongings or seasonal items - accessed from upstairs bedroom. Adding to the charm and functionality of this dwelling is a heated & cooled sun room at the back of the home, bathing the space in natural light and offering a perfect spot to unwind and enjoy sunny Florida. Also downstairs is an office/study, formal dining room, and a spacious half bath just off the foyer. This home seamlessly blends classic architecture with modern conveniences, making it a true gem.
